cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with image recognition using a novel neural network architecture and loss functions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The proposed architecture and loss functions are designed to address the challenges of limited information content in VLR images, which involves intelligent decision-making, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. The paper also involves experiments with face recognition, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves the use of auxiliary data during training, which involves optimization techniques, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category.
